ss which prevented them from worki\nng and being able to pay their bi\nlls, to a flooded home.  In 2012 we responded to more than 8\n million telephone calls fo\nr sales, enquiries and renewals\n.\nInsurers are delivering on their commitment to reduce car insurance premiums&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nMedical Evidence &amp; Rehabilitation&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Medical Report Fees&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Small Claims Track Limit&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nPeriod of Whiplash InjuryTariff Standard AwardVery minor &lt; a few days\n£0 (No damages)\nMore than very minor but less than 3 months\n£250\n3 to 6 months\n£500\n6 months to 12 months\n£1000\n&gt;12 \nmonths symptoms\nStandard Award\n&#xa0;\nPre Medical Offers&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Cash inducements should be banned for all stakeholders to help combat fraudulent and exaggerated claims &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Fraud     Data Sharing&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n     Exaggerated Claims&#xa0;\n     Sentencing Guidelines&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n     “Strike Out” Fraud Claims&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nDecember 2013\n \n&#xa0;\n The agreement allows for two rates of payment: Rate B is the standard rate; and Rate A is a discounted rate that factors in early payment (within 90 days). It is estimated by Medical Reporting Organisations (MROs) that around 75% of all \nmedical reports \nprepared in R\noad\n Traffic Accident \ncases valued at up to £15,000 are obtained via MROs who are signatories to the Agreement.\n"